,"meanings":["Scottish: apparently a spelling pronunciation of <i>Vans</i>, a misreading of <i>Vaus</i> (see   Vause  ), in which <i>-u-</i> has been miscopied as <i>-n-</i>. If true, it is probably limited to the Vans or Vaus family of Wigtownshire. It may be this surname that appears in Ireland from the early 17th century, especially in Ulster, but it could alternatively be the English name in 2 below.","English: if not a transcription error for   Vause   (a surname well evidenced in Warwickshire and Leicestershire), a variant of   Vann  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Vause","meanings":["English (Yorkshire and Lancashire):","of Norman origin, a habitational name from Vaux (see   Vaux  ), a common French placename, singular and plural of <i>val</i> ‘valley’, the plural form being Latinized in surnames as <i>de Vallibus</i>. Norman lords with this surname are recorded in 12th- and early 13th-century records in Cumberland (Irthington), Devon (Farwood, in Colyton), East Yorkshire (Warter), Essex (Belchamp), and Leicestershire (Belvoir). Compare   Vale  .","nickname perhaps from Middle English <i>fals</i>, <i>faus</i>, <i>vaus</i> (Old French <i>fals</i>, <i>faus</i>, Old English <i>fals</i>) ‘deceitful, disloyal, dishonest, mendacious’, but it is more likely the name arises from 1, with the common Anglo-Norman French substitution of <i>le</i> for <i>de</i> in their surname."]}]},{"name":"Beatrix","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Late Latin personal name, which was borne by a saint martyred in Rome, together with Saints Faustinus and Simplicius, in the early 4th century. The original form of the name was probably <i>Viatrix</i>, a feminine version of <i>Viator</i> ‘voyager (through life)’, which was a favourite name among early Christians. This was then altered by association with Latin <i>Beatus</i> ‘blessed’ (<i>Via-</i> and <i>Bea-</i> sometimes being pronounced the same in Late Latin).  See also  Beatrice ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Beatrix de Vanne was born in 1187, in Blisworth, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Ralph de Sandford about 1219, in Askham, Westmorland, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"1187–":"1187–Surnud","1199–1250":"1199–1250","1209–1249":"1209–1249","1218–1311":"1218–1311","1187–Female":"1187–Surnud","1249":"1249","about 1219":"umbes 1219","1311":"1311","1199":"1199","1187":"1187","1250":"1250","1209":"1209","1218":"1218","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","Blisworth, South Northamptonshire district, Northampton, England, United Kingdom":"Blisworth, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sandford, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Askham, Westmorland, England":"Askham, Westmorland, England"},"fi":{"1187–":"1187–Kuollut","1199–1250":"1199–1250","1209–1249":"1209–1249","1218–1311":"1218–1311","1187–Female":"1187–Kuollut","1249":"1249","about 1219":"noin 1219","1311":"1311","1199":"1199","1187":"1187","1250":"1250","1209":"1209","1218":"1218","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","Blisworth, South Northamptonshire district, Northampton, England, United Kingdom":"Blisworth, Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Sandford, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Askham, Westmorland, England":"Askham, Westmorland, England"},"fr":{"1187–":"1187–Décédée","1199–1250":"1199–1250","1209–1249":"1209–1249","1218–1311":"1218–1311","1187–Female":"1187–Décédée","1249":"1249","about 1219":"environ 1219","1311":"1311","1199":"1199","1187":"1187","1250":"1250","1209":"1209","1218":"1218","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Angleterre","Blisworth, South Northamptonshire district, Northamp